                  </hi>. I am shopman to Mr. Charles Howton Clarke, of Lime-street. On the 27th of February Chapman brought roe some money—I went into the shop to give him change, and found the prisoner an his hands and knees, and the till drawn out—I took hold of him, and he took two sovereigns and two half-sovereigns out of his mouth, and I took them.</p>
